From: switch-tools <noreply@example.invalid>
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] bink2: fix scalar IDCT-add fallback + cpu-feature probe

Two compile-time issues that prevent the scalar fallback path from
building on non-x86 targets:

  1. `Bk2IdctAddDcOnly` calls an undefined `Clip255` helper. Substitute
     the existing `ClipInt(..., 0, 255)` used elsewhere in the file.
  2. `Bk2CpuHasAvx2` calls `__builtin_cpu_init` / `__builtin_cpu_supports`
     unconditionally on GCC/Clang, but those builtins are only valid on
     x86 targets. Guard them so non-x86 builds fall through to the
     scalar path.

Both are pure scalar-path bugs that the x86-on-x86 CI never exercises;
they don't affect the SIMD paths.

Same patches that we apply for our ARM POC build; they're toolchain-
agnostic. (Renamed from "wasm" → just "scalar" for clarity.)
---
 bink2/bink2_video.cpp | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bink2/bink2_video.cpp b/bink2/bink2_video.cpp
--- a/bink2/bink2_video.cpp
+++ b/bink2/bink2_video.cpp
@@ -323,7 +323,7 @@ static bool Bk2CpuHasAvx2()
 {
     int cached = g_bk2_simd_runtime.avx2_available.load(std::memory_order_acquire);
     if (cached != -1) return cached != 0;
-#if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
+#if (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)) && (defined(__x86_64__) || defined(__i386__))
     __builtin_cpu_init();
     const int v = __builtin_cpu_supports("avx2") ? 1 : 0;
 #else
@@ -739,7 +739,7 @@ static inline void Bk2IdctAddDcOnly(uint8_t* dst, int stride, const int16_t* blo
     const int16_t v = (int16_t)v32;
     for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
         for (int j = 0; j < 8; ++j) {
-            dst[j] = Clip255((int32_t)dst[j] + v);
+            dst[j] = (uint8_t)ClipInt((int32_t)dst[j] + v, 0, 255);
         }
         dst += stride;
     }
